    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="152"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>152. Note From President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> to
                    Multiple Recipients<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d152fn1">Source: Carter
                        Library, Papers of <persName corresp="#p_MWF_1">Walter F.
                        Mondale</persName>, Box 206, Middle East/Panama, (7/1–12/31/1977). No
                        classification marking. Sent to <persName corresp="#p_MWF_1"
                            >Mondale</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_JH_1">Jordan</persName>, and
                            <persName corresp="#p_MF_2">Moore</persName>. A notation on the letter
                        reads: “The V.P. has seen.” Unknown hands wrote: “<hi rend="italic">No
                            copies,</hi>” “<persName corresp="#p_BEW_1">Brooke</persName> 1:30,” and
                        “[illegible] w/ Saul” at the top of the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-03-12">March 12, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>To <persName corresp="#p_HEF_1">Fritz</persName>, Ham, <persName
                            corresp="#p_CF_1">Frank</persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d152fn2">An unknown hand placed a checkmark by
                                “<persName corresp="#p_CF_1">Frank</persName>.”</note>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>After calling 15 of the apparently hopeless Senators, I believe we should
                    redouble efforts—including personal conversation by V.P. with:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BQN_1">Burdick</persName> “Wants debt service data”<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d152fn3">An unknown hand placed a checkmark in the left
                        margin. An unknown hand wrote and circled in the right margin: “1:00
                            <persName corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName>.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CH_1">Cannon</persName> “Will talk to <persName
                        corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_NSJ_1"
                        >Nunn</persName>”<note n="4" xml:id="d152fn4">An unknown hand placed a
                        checkmark in the left margin and underlined “will take to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_NSJ_1"
                            >Nunn</persName>.” A different unknown hand wrote: “<gloss
                            target="#t_VP_1">VP</gloss>” in the left margin and circled “<persName
                            corresp="#p_CH_1">Cannon</persName>” and “to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_NSJ_1"
                            >Nunn</persName>.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>Melchor “Giving further consideration”</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DR_1">Dole</persName>—“Haven’t closed door”<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d152fn5">An unknown hand placed a checkmark in the left margin. A
                        different unknown hand wrote “Straus” in the left margin and circled
                            “<persName corresp="#p_DR_1">Dole</persName>.” A different unknown hand
                        wrote in the right margin: “Shirley.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_YAJ_1">Young</persName>—“Don’t give up on me”<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d152fn6">An unknown hand placed a checkmark in the left margin and
                        wrote: “<hi rend="italic">No</hi>.” A different unknown hand wrote in the
                        left margin: “<gloss target="#t_VP_1">VP</gloss>”.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Domenici—“Will talk to <persName corresp="#p_NSJ_1">Nunn</persName>, call
                        Mon.”<note n="7" xml:id="d152fn7">An unknown hand placed a checkmark in the
                        left margin. A different unknown hand wrote “<gloss target="#t_VP_1"
                            >VP</gloss>” in the left margin and circled “Domenici” and “<persName
                            corresp="#p_NSJ_1">Nunn</persName>.”</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0428" n="393" xml:id="pg_393"/>
                <p>Hansen—“Will see Pres before ‘No’ vote”<note n="8" xml:id="d152fn8">An unknown
                        hand wrote in the left margin: “<gloss target="#t_VP_1">VP</gloss>”.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RWV_1">Roth</persName>—“Still giving thought”<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d152fn9">An unknown hand wrote in the left margin: “<hi
                            rend="italic">No</hi>.” A different unknown hand circled “<persName
                            corresp="#p_RWV_1">Roth</persName>.” A different unknown hand wrote and
                        circled “strongly committed” in the right margin.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Hopeless: Stevens, Johnston, Bartlett, Griffin, <persName corresp="#p_GB_1"
                        >Goldwater</persName>, Lupor.<note n="10" xml:id="d152fn10">An unknown hand
                        wrote beneath the note: “Straus—Zorinksy,” “Straus Chris—<persName
                            corresp="#p_DDW_1">DeConcini</persName>,” “<persName corresp="#p_HM_1"
                            >Hatfield</persName>—<persName corresp="#p_MWM_1">Mansfield</persName>
                            (<persName corresp="#p_SJC_1">Stennis</persName>) Nun→<persName
                            corresp="#p_HM_1">Hatfield</persName> (By <gloss target="#t_FM_1"
                            >FM</gloss>),” “<persName corresp="#p_NSJ_1"
                            >Nunn</persName>—Belmon—<gloss target="#t_FM_1">FM</gloss>→NUNN—Back
                        tonight” and “Chris-<gloss target="#t_VP_1">VP</gloss>—<persName
                            corresp="#p_BEW_1">Brooke</persName>—.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">J.C.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
